    • Method Detail

      • getDisabledEvents

        DESEventSet getDisabledEvents​(FSAState state)
        Returns the events disabled at a given state. If the control map is undefined (e.g., not computed yet or out of synch with the rest of the models), this method should return null.
        Parameters:
        state - state of the supervisor
        Returns:
        the events disabled at a given state; or null if the control map is undefined

      • setDisabledEvents

        void setDisabledEvents​(FSAState state,
                       DESEventSet set)
        Sets the events disabled at a given state.
        Parameters:
        state - state of the supervisor
        set - set of disabled events for this state
